<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb5603877-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s925"><num value="925">§ 925.</num><heading> Border Patrol unit for United States Virgin Islands</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idb5603878-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s925/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may establish at least 1 Border Patrol unit for the United States Virgin Islands.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idb5603879-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s925/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Report</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 180 days after <date date="2006-10-13">October 13, 2006</date>, the Secretary shall submit a report to the appropriate congressional committees that includes the schedule, if any, for carrying out subsection (a).</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idb560387a-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/347/tI/s126">Pub. L. 109–347, title I, § 126</ref>, <date date="2006-10-13">Oct. 13, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1900">120 Stat. 1900</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
